cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS 

This paper deals with distributed protocols for exchanging information among agents, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). It also involves the study of graph connectivity, which is a topic in network science (cs.SI) and graph theory (cs.DS). The use of telephone numbers as identities for agents falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). Finally, the paper deals with the characterization of success in terms of graph topology, which is a topic in systems and control theory (cs.SY).
